your body into a pod

27:36.455 --> 27:38.624
and plant you as fertilizer
for a tree,

27:38.657 --> 27:39.859
and that's what I want.

27:39.892 --> 27:41.593
What?
Mom, don't be morose.

27:41.627 --> 27:43.796
It's not morose.
It's what I want.

27:43.830 --> 27:45.932
I want to be a tree
that you and the kids

27:45.965 --> 27:49.736
and all the grandkids
can picnic under.

27:49.769 --> 27:53.572
I want to make oxygen
and fight global warming.

27:53.605 --> 27:55.641
I don't want to
become pollution,

27:55.674 --> 27:59.812
and that's what a casket is,
and that's what cremation is.

27:59.846 --> 28:03.415
It's land pollution,
and it's air pollution.

28:03.449 --> 28:07.920
If I die today,
or when I die whenever,

28:07.954 --> 28:13.025
just remember, sweetheart,
I want to be a tree.

28:13.059 --> 28:15.061
I want to watch
over our family.

28:17.263 --> 28:18.630
Forever.

28:18.664 --> 28:19.899
You ready?

28:23.602 --> 28:25.004
I'm ready.

28:40.086 --> 28:41.387
It's a no.

28:42.889 --> 28:44.390
Uh, you said it's a no?

28:44.423 --> 28:46.392
Dr. Millin, would you like
to close the chest?

28:46.425 --> 28:49.695
What?
The heart has hematomas everywhere.

28:49.728 --> 28:52.164
It is not usable
for transplant.

28:52.198 --> 28:54.000
I can close,
Dr. Pierce.

28:54.033 --> 28:56.635
Nonsense. She knows how to do
a running subcuticular stitch.

28:56.668 --> 28:59.671
I'm sure she's practiced
on a thousand oranges.

28:59.705 --> 29:01.373
Human flesh
is a little bit firmer.

29:01.407 --> 29:02.775
You're gonna have to pull
a little bit harder.

29:02.809 --> 29:04.210
Uh, what about Howard?

29:04.243 --> 29:06.245
You'll explain to Howard
and his husband

29:06.278 --> 29:07.914
that Howard will remain
on the transplant list,

29:07.947 --> 29:09.248
but today was not his day.

29:09.281 --> 29:10.616
B-But his husband
couldn't stop crying.

29:10.649 --> 29:12.384
I know. It sucks.

29:12.418 --> 29:14.420
But we take the good
with the bad here, Dr. Millin.

29:14.453 --> 29:16.889
Schmitt, keep an eye.

29:18.357 --> 29:21.727
O-Okay.
Um, 4-0 Monocryl, please.

29:21.760 --> 29:23.229
You say please to Bokhee!

29:23.262 --> 29:25.697
I did.

29:25.731 --> 29:27.199
Right here. There.

29:27.233 --> 29:28.634
They just keep
getting younger.

29:28.667 --> 29:29.701
Right?

29:34.974 --> 29:36.809
Adams, what are you doing?

29:36.843 --> 29:39.378
I screwed up. I just want
to make sure she's okay.

29:39.411 --> 29:41.747
You want to scrub in?
For real?

29:41.780 --> 29:43.782
