I'm getting fired later.

29:45.584 --> 29:47.786
Well, if they haven't fired you
yet, you still got a shot.

29:49.121 --> 29:50.622
Look, here's the deal.

29:50.656 --> 29:52.258
We all have bad days.
We all make mistakes.

29:52.291 --> 29:53.625
You just got to learn
from them.

29:53.659 --> 29:55.227
You learn from them,
you're good.

29:55.261 --> 29:56.595
Right?
What'd you learn today?

29:56.628 --> 29:58.130
Uh.

29:58.164 --> 30:00.099
Raise my hand
before talking,

30:00.132 --> 30:01.868
save the shame
for the end of the day,

30:01.901 --> 30:04.736
and use full names
when speaking with next of kin.

30:04.770 --> 30:06.405
Yes. Okay.

30:06.438 --> 30:07.874
That's good.

30:07.907 --> 30:10.376
Come on.

30:10.409 --> 30:12.478
End your day better
than it started.

30:12.511 --> 30:14.713
Okay? Let's go.

30:14.746 --> 30:16.548
Come on, let's go!

30:28.928 --> 30:31.297
Okay, so this is going to be
a long, arduous surgery.

30:31.330 --> 30:32.965
Let's pace ourselves.

30:32.999 --> 30:35.367
And say a prayer now
if you're the praying kind.

30:35.401 --> 30:37.369
The donor is Liam Collins.

30:37.403 --> 30:39.906
He loved rugby,
and he loved science.

30:39.939 --> 30:42.909
The recipient is Sarah Martinez,
and she loves nature,

30:42.942 --> 30:45.211
and she's about to be
a grandmother.

30:45.244 --> 30:47.413
It's a beautiful day
to save lives.

30:49.448 --> 30:51.617
It's a beautiful day
to save lives.

